## Authentication and Authorisation

Learn about the user-restricted <a href="/api-documentation/docs/authorisation/user-restricted-endpoints" rel="noopener noreferrer">authentication</a> used by the API.

HMRC supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating user restricted API requests using an OAuth 2.0 Bearer Token in the AUTHORIZATION header. Find out more about [Authorisation](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/authorisation).

Flow type: authorizationCode

Authorization URL: https://api.service.hmrc.gov.uk/oauth/authorize

Token URL: https://api.service.hmrc.gov.uk/oauth/token

Refresh URL: https://api.service.hmrc.gov.uk/oauth/refresh

Required scopes: TBA

